LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places called Elton (Berkshire, Cheshire, Derbyshire, Durham, Herefordshire, Huntingdonshire, Lancashire, and Nottinghamshire). The Eltons in Chesire, Derbyshire, and Durham are from Old English <i>ǣl</i> ‘eel’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’. Elton in Berkshire is from the Old English female personal name <i>Æthelflǣd</i> (composed of the elements <i>æthel</i> ‘noble’ + <i>flǣd</i> ‘beauty’). Both Elton in Herefordshire and in Nottinghamshire are from the Old English personal name <i>Ella</i> + <i>tūn</i>. The Berkshire origin for the surname is especially well represented.","Norwegian: habitational name from a farm name in eastern Norway, in Old Norse <i>Elgjartún</i> ‘enclosed sacred place’ (or fenced in for <i>elg</i> ‘moose’?)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Elton had at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1160":"1160"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1160":"1160"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1160":"1160","lifeSummary":"Elton a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1160":"1160","lifeSummary":"Elton hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1160–Male":"1160–Desede","–Male":"Desede","1160":"1160"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1160–Male":"1160–elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","1160":"1160"},"id":{"–":"Telah Meninggal","1160–Male":"1160–Telah Meninggal","–Male":"Telah Meninggal","1160":"1160"},"it":{"–":"Deceduto","1160–Male":"1160–Deceduto","–Male":"Deceduto","1160":"1160","lifeSummary":"Elton lui avuto almeno 1 figlio."},"ja":{"–":"死亡","1160–Male":"1160年–死亡","–Male":"死亡","1160":"1160年","lifeSummary":"Eltonは少なくとも1人の息子をもうけた。"},"ko":{"–":"사망","1160–Male":"1160년–사망","–Male":"사망","1160":"1160년","lifeSummary":"Elton(은)는 적어도 한 명의 아들을 두었다."},"lv":{"–":"miris","11